result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Case called along with 13CF389, 13CF429, and 14CF1.  Defendant Nathan D. Braaksma in court with attorney Michael Devitt for Katherine Koepsell.  Yolanda J Tienstra appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   An Amended Information was filed in 13CF318, amending the charge to Misd. Battery.  The Court reviewed CPR and PQWOR; Ct. heard plea in 13CF318 of No Contest to the amended charge of Misd. Battery.  In 13CF389, the Court heard plea of No Contest to felony Bail Jumping. Court found sufficient facts. The Court found his pleas were given FKVI, accepted the pleas and found Defendant Guilty of Misd. Battery in 13CF318. The Court approved the DPA in 13CF389.  ADA and Attorney Devitt signed the DPA document in the Courtroom.  In 13CF429, this is to be dismissed and read in.  As to 14CF1, this is to be dismissed and read in.  As to the uncharged DA case, 2014DD343, those possible charges are to be read in.  The Court questioned the DA regarding the victim rights and found they are compliant.  Restitution to be held open at this time and the Court made no ruling.  The Court heard from the State and Defense and sentenced him as follows:  

In 13CF318: S/W, probation for 2 years with conditions: $200 fine plus costs; the defendant is to provide his PA with a copy of his AODA assessment; defendant shall comply with AODA treatment/counseling. Absolute sobriety.  No bars, etc.  Within two weeks, defendant must must enroll in alcohol counseling.  Restitution to be held open. 
13CF389: Felony Bail Jumping x 1:  DPA with terms 
13CF429: Felony Bail Jumping x 2:  Dismissed and read in with 13CF318
14CF1: Felony Bail Jumping x 3:  Dismissed and read in with 13CF318 
DA Case #2014DD343, possible multiple counts of Bail Jumping: Uncharged Read in (City of Horicon): to be read in
Court reserved the right to hear possible expungement at the restitution hearing scheduled for 3-25-14.
Plea/sentencing hearing on February 20, 2014 at 03:30 pm.
Preliminary hearing on January 30, 2014 at 03:00 pm.

Defendant  in court with attorney Katherine Koepsell.  James T Sempf appeared for the State of Wisconsin .  Defendant makes statements to the court regarding efforts to obtain counsel.  Defendant sworn and testified.  Court finds defendant is not indigent and denies request for counsel.

Defendant shall not consume alcohol or other intoxicants.  Defendant must maintain absolute sobriety  and shall not go upon the premises of any establishment whose primary business activity involves the sale or distribution of alcoholic beverages, including bars, taverns, liquor stores and beer tents.  The Jail shall permit Defendant to make a phone call at the county expense for bail purposes.
